    <article class="about-copy">
      <p>Each neighborhood has its own character, concerns, and priorities. WPCNA exists to help those neighborhoods stay connected to each other, to the city, and to what’s happening across White Plains.</p>

      <p>This site is part of that effort.</p>

      <p>It’s a simple, public guide to life in White Plains: events, meetings, local organizations, and the neighborhoods that shape the city. The goal is to make it easier to see what’s going on and find your way into it.</p>

      <p>White Plains is the county seat of Westchester and a growing city with a busy downtown and a wide range of residential neighborhoods. What happens here isn’t limited to one part of the city, and it doesn’t always show up in one place. This site brings those pieces together.</p>

      <p>WPCNA itself is made up of representatives from neighborhood associations throughout White Plains. It serves as a forum for sharing information, raising concerns, and keeping communication open between neighborhoods and the broader community.</p>

      <p>If you’re looking to get a better sense of what’s happening in White Plains, or simply want to stay connected to your part of it, you’re in the right place.</p>
    </article>

